column5: Hi ,  Headin up to Simcoe on Wed. Ice fished once lasrt year out of Beaverton with a freinds ATV.Just wondering where a good place to walk out from might be.Coming up from the south.I've looked at hydro maps and followed the threads.Is it worth my while to leave from the public parking @ Willow Beach?   Thanks
You can walk out pretty much anywhere around Simcoe, were there is access. All depends what your fishing for. Just watch were you park!!!!! AND Make sure the ice is safe!!!!! Good Luck
What did you want to catch?
I think my nephew would be happy with a feed of perch.Is Innisfil busy during the week?

if it's perch you want, walk out from Gilford... start at 10-12 ft and work your way out as the day goes on... 20-25 ft by mid day. Be careful where you park there and yes... minnows are available there should you require. HH
